<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <%=headerTags%>
    <title>ClearanceManagement.com</title>
    <style type="text/css">
    </style>
</head>
<body ng-app="safeApp" ng-controller="controller">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="panel panel-primary" style="height: auto; margin-top: 35px">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h1>Welcome to ClearanceManagement.com</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <h3>
                    Get Employed - Help Your Employees
                </h3>
                <div class="small">
                    We create your professional digital portfolio to assist you with Pennsylvania district releases and clearances for submission to unlimited potential employers.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
                <div class="panel panel-info">
                    <div class="panel-heading">
                        <span>Volunteers</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>
Under PA Code Volunteers are required to have their clearances completed every five years.  
Using ClearanceManagement.com, you can store, submit and recover your clearances electronically 
as well as file them with the appropriate school, district, or institution so that you can
concentrate on volunterring!
						</p>
                        <div>
                            <button type="button" onclick="window.location = '<%=createUrl('UserSignup')%>';" class="btn btn-sm btn-info">
                                Click Here to Get Started
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
                <div class="panel panel-info">
                    <div class="panel-heading">
                        <span>Educators</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>
Under PA Code employees are required to have their clearances
completed every five years.  This program will let you store, submit (and recover) 
your clearances electronically as well as file them with the appropriate school, 
district  or institution so that you can concentrate on working.  Additionally, this 
program will notify you and your employer when you are coming up on renewal for 
your clearances across the life time of your career.
                        </p>
                        <div>
                            <button type="button" onclick="window.location = '<%=createUrl('UserSignup')%>';" class="btn btn-sm btn-info">
                                Click Here to Sign Up
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
                <div class="panel panel-warning">
                    <div class="panel-heading">
                        <span>Find Out More</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>
ClearanceManagement.com is your one-stop solution for managing your clearances.
Still have questions?  Click below to find out more about how we can help you stay
up-to-date.
                        </p>
                        <div>
                            <button type="button" onclick="window.location = '<%=createUrl('About')%>';" class="btn btn-sm btn-warning">
                                Learn More About Us
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
                <div class="panel panel-success">
                    <div class="panel-heading">
                        <span>Existing Users</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>
                            If you're already a user, welcome back!  Use the button below
							to enter your login credentials and sign in.
                        </p>
                        <div>
                            <button type="button" onclick="window.location = '<%=createUrl('Login')%>';" class="btn btn-sm btn-success">
                                Click to Log In
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>